  <title>
Max Grossman
  </title>
  <content>
   <para id="gd-idp2344">
Max Grossman is an undergraduate student majoring in Computer Science with a focus in Parallel and Distributed Computing at Rice University, graduating in May 2012.
   </para>
   <para id="gd-idp2984">
While a student, he has been involved in the Rice Center for Engineering Leadership (RCEL) as a student advisor, the Rice Robotics Club as a programmer, and the Rice University ACM Programming Team.
   </para>
   <para id="gd-idm40752">
As a professional software developer and researcher, Max has held positions in international institutions of academia, industry, and government including
    <link url="http://habanero.rice.edu" window="new">
Rice University's Habanero Multicore Software Research Project
    </link>
, Repsol USA, NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory, the Shuttleworth Foundation, the Department of Defense, and the Indian Institute of Technology in Kanpur. For more information on Max's responsibilities at each of these organizations, please refer to his
    <link url="resume.pdf" window="new">
resume
    </link>
.
   </para>
   <para id="gd-idm38624">
Max's current duties include being an undergraduate researcher and full time student at Rice University, parallelizing computational models for the Astrophysics &amp; Space Sciences Divison at NASA JPL, applying multicore architectures to computational challenges in Repsol USA's geophysics R&amp;D division, developing a content importer for the Connexions eduction project, and acting as lead developer at
    <link url="wisga.com" window="new">
Wisga.com
    </link>
.
   </para>
   <para id="gd-idm40856">
In addition to his experience in high performance and scientific computing, Max is also interested in novel techniques for human-computer interaction. This interest has manifested itself in side projects with the
    <link url="http://www.xbox.com/en-US/kinect" window="new">
Microsoft Kinect
    </link>
and
    <link url="emotiv.com" window="new">
Emotiv EPOC
    </link>
.
   </para>
